  // Hide the loader and show the page content
  document.body.classList.remove("loading");
});
```

In this example, the indicator is initially hidden using CSS, and then shown using the `.loading` class when the page starts loading. Once the `window.onload` event fires, the `.loading` class is removed and the content is displayed.

You can customize the loading indicator CSS and HTML to suit your needs.

